docs.abstract: Trump won on the politics of racial backlash. Now he’s following through with an agenda meant to stoke it further.
docs.snippet: Trump won on the politics of racial backlash. Now he’s following through with an agenda meant to stoke it further.
docs.lead_paragraph: White resentment put Donald Trump in the White House. And there is every indication that it will keep him there, especially as he continues to transform that seething, irrational fear about an increasingly diverse America into policies that feed his supporters’ worst racial anxieties.

docs.abstract: Nearly a dozen federal agencies — even the Transportation Security Administration — were sent to Washington and other cities after the president vowed to “dominate” protesters.
docs.snippet: Nearly a dozen federal agencies — even the Transportation Security Administration — were sent to Washington and other cities after the president vowed to “dominate” protesters.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s vow to “dominate” demonstrators protesting police brutality has mobilized the full might of federal law enforcement, from border agencies and the Drug Enforcement Administration to F.B.I. hostage rescue teams, working alongside local law enforcement, the military police and the National Guard.

headline.main: Trump Deploys the Full Might of Federal Law Enforcement to Crush Protests
headline.print_headline: Washington, With No Governor, Becomes Test for Federal Enforcement

docs.abstract: Mr. Heyward became an activist after his 13-year-old son, who was playing with a toy gun, was killed by a police officer in Brooklyn in 1994.
docs.snippet: Mr. Heyward became an activist after his 13-year-old son, who was playing with a toy gun, was killed by a police officer in Brooklyn in 1994.
docs.lead_paragraph: One September evening in 1994, Nicholas Heyward Jr., 13, was playing cops and robbers with friends on a rooftop at the Gowanus Houses, the Brooklyn housing project where he lived. The boys, carrying toy guns, decided to go back inside and rushed down the stairs, jostling one another.

headline.main: Nicholas Heyward Sr., 61, Dies; Spoke Out Against Police Brutality
headline.print_headline: Nicholas Heyward Sr., 61, Police Brutality Protester
